End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 9: DER length helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
DER length encoding rules (X.690 8.1.3):
  - 0..127: single byte
  - 128..255: 0x81 followed by length byte
  - 256..65535: 0x82 followed by 2 BE bytes
  - 65536..16777215: 0x83 followed by 3 BE bytes
  - etc.
This helper writes the length and returns the number of bytes consumed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on the length value and write the appropriate form.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1). At most 5 bytes written.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Encoding metadata; non-secret.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_write_der_length" takes out_buffer as Integer, out_offset as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    If length is less than 128:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset, length)
        Return 1
    End If
    If length is less than 256:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset, 129)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 1, length)
        Return 2
    End If
    If length is less than 65536:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset, 130)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 1, (length divided by 256) modulo by 256)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 2, length modulo by 256)
        Return 3
    End If
    If length is less than 16777216:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset, 131)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 1, (length divided by 65536) modulo by 256)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 2, (length divided by 256) modulo by 256)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 3, length modulo by 256)
        Return 4
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset, 132)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 1, (length divided by 16777216) modulo by 256)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 2, (length divided by 65536) modulo by 256)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 3, (length divided by 256) modulo by 256)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset plus 4, length modulo by 256)
    Return 5
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper that returns the number of bytes a DER length encoding will
consume without writing anything. Used for pre-allocation sizing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirrors keypair_write_der_length but returns the byte count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret encoding metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_der_length_bytes" takes length as Integer returns Integer:
    If length is less than 128:
        Return 1
    End If
    If length is less than 256:
        Return 2
    End If
    If length is less than 65536:
        Return 3
    End If
    If length is less than 16777216:
        Return 4
    End If
    Return 5
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 10: keypair_serialize_pkcs8 - PKCS#8 PrivateKeyInfo encoding
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Encode a KeyPair's private half as a PKCS#8 PrivateKeyInfo DER blob per
RFC 5958. The structure is:

  SEQUENCE (tag 0x30) {
    INTEGER 0                              -- version (3 bytes: 02 01 00)
    SEQUENCE (AlgorithmIdentifier) {
      OBJECT IDENTIFIER algorithm
      -- parameters: NULL for RSA, absent for Ed25519/Ed448/X25519/X448,
      --             namedCurve OID for ECDSA
    }
    OCTET STRING privateKey                -- algorithm-specific inner encoding
  }

For Ed25519/Ed448/X25519/X448 per RFC 8410, the privateKey OCTET STRING
contains another OCTET STRING wrapping the raw scalar: an outer 0x04
length-prefixed wrapping holds an inner 0x04 length-prefixed CurvePrivateKey.

For RSA, the privateKey OCTET STRING holds the PKCS#1 RSAPrivateKey
DER blob (RFC 8017 Appendix A.1.2).

For ECDSA, the privateKey OCTET STRING holds the SEC 1 ECPrivateKey blob
(RFC 5915).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Get the algorithm tag and private bytes from the keypair.
  2. Compute the sizes of each inner element.
  3. Build the SEQUENCE inside-out:
     - inner_alg_seq: SEQUENCE { OID, optional params }
     - private_octet: OCTET STRING { algorithm-specific encoding }
     - outer_seq: SEQUENCE { 02 01 00, alg_seq, private_octet }
  4. Allocate a single output buffer, write the outer SEQUENCE header
     followed by the inner bytes.
  5. Return the buffer pointer and stash the total length at the start.

For v0.0.8.5, full PKCS#8 emission is implemented for the Ed25519/Ed448/
X25519/X448 family (RFC 8410). ECDSA and RSA emission are explicit DER
constructions using the SubjectPublicKeyInfo path for the public half.

Output format: [4 BE total_len][... DER bytes ...]
The caller dereferences out_buffer+4 for the DER bytes and reads the
length from out_buffer[0..3] (big-endian int32).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(private_key_byte_length). One pass write.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The DER blob holds the private key material. Caller is responsible for
secure storage and zeroization after use.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_serialize_pkcs8" takes arena as Integer, kp as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kp is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let algorithm be KP.keypair_algorithm(kp)
    Let sk be KP.keypair_private(kp)
    If sk is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let priv_bytes be SK.private_key_secret_bytes_internal(sk)
    Let priv_len be SK.private_key_byte_length(sk)
    If priv_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: RFC 8410 curve family: emit RFC 5958 form.
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ED25519:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_curve_8410(arena, algorithm, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ED448:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_curve_8410(arena, algorithm, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_X25519:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_curve_8410(arena, algorithm, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_X448:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_curve_8410(arena, algorithm, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    End If

    Note: ECDSA: build the RFC 5915 ECPrivateKey SEQUENCE inside the
    Note: privateKey OCTET STRING. The public key is sourced from the
    Note: KeyPair's PublicKey side.
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P256:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_ecdsa(arena, algorithm, kp, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P384:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_ecdsa(arena, algorithm, kp, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P521:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_ecdsa(arena, algorithm, kp, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    End If

    Note: RSA: build the RFC 8017 RSAPrivateKey SEQUENCE inside the
    Note: privateKey OCTET STRING.
    If Alg.rsa_alg_modulus_bytes(algorithm) is not equal to 0:
        Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_rsa(arena, algorithm, sk)
    End If

    Note: PQ algorithms (ML-KEM, ML-DSA, SLH-DSA): PKCS#8 wrapping is
    Note: not standardized at the same level as the classical families;
    Note: emit the algorithm OID and a raw OCTET STRING of the key bytes.
    Note: The pair round-trips through keypair_deserialize_pkcs8 for
    Note: in-tree consumers via algorithm-driven dispatch.
    Return keypair_serialize_pkcs8_pq(arena, algorithm, priv_bytes, priv_len)
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper that emits the RFC 8410 PKCS#8 form for the curve-25519/448
family. The inner OCTET STRING wraps another OCTET STRING (CurvePrivateKey)
containing the raw scalar bytes. For Ed25519 the raw scalar is the 32-byte
seed (NOT the 64-byte expanded form); we extract the first 32 bytes of
the stored expanded key.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Constructs:
  SEQUENCE {
    INTEGER 0
    SEQUENCE { OID algorithm }                   -- no parameters
    OCTET STRING {
      OCTET STRING { raw_scalar_bytes }
    }
  }
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(scalar_length). One pass.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Carries the private scalar; caller wipes after use.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_serialize_pkcs8_curve_8410" takes arena as Integer, algorithm as Integer, priv_bytes as Integer, priv_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: For Ed25519 the seed is the first 32 bytes of the 64-byte expansion.
    Let scalar_len be priv_len
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ED25519:
        Set scalar_len to 32
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ED448:
        Set scalar_len to 57
    End If

    Note: Inner CurvePrivateKey = OCTET STRING { scalar_len bytes }.
    Let inner_octet_len be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(scalar_len) plus scalar_len

    Note: privateKey OCTET STRING wraps the inner_octet.
    Let private_octet_content_len be inner_octet_len
    Let private_octet_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(private_octet_content_len) plus private_octet_content_len

    Note: AlgorithmIdentifier SEQUENCE { OID } -- 5 bytes for the OID.
    Let oid_total be 5
    Let alg_seq_content_len be oid_total
    Let alg_seq_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(alg_seq_content_len) plus alg_seq_content_len

    Note: version INTEGER 0 = 02 01 00.
    Let version_total be 3

    Let outer_content_len be version_total plus alg_seq_total plus private_octet_total
    Let outer_header_len be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(outer_content_len)
    Let outer_total be outer_header_len plus outer_content_len

    Note: Allocate buffer with 4-byte length prefix.
    Let buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 4 plus outer_total)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int32(buf, 0, outer_total)
    Let off be 4
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, outer_content_len)

    Note: version INTEGER 0.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 1, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 2, 0)
    Set off to off plus 3

    Note: AlgorithmIdentifier SEQUENCE.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, alg_seq_content_len)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_oid(algorithm, buf, off)

    Note: privateKey OCTET STRING.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 4)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, private_octet_content_len)

    Note: inner OCTET STRING with the raw scalar.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 4)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, scalar_len)
    Memory.memory_copy(buf plus off, priv_bytes, scalar_len)
    Set off to off plus scalar_len

    Return buf
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper that writes the named-curve OID for the supplied ECDSA algorithm.
Returns the number of bytes written; the curve OIDs are:
  P-256: 1.2.840.10045.3.1.7  -> 06 08 2A 86 48 CE 3D 03 01 07 (10 bytes)
  P-384: 1.3.132.0.34         -> 06 05 2B 81 04 00 22         (7 bytes)
  P-521: 1.3.132.0.35         -> 06 05 2B 81 04 00 23         (7 bytes)
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on algorithm tag and emit the canonical DER bytes for the
namedCurve OID. Returns 0 for any non-ECDSA algorithm.
