@Reasoning
Encode an unsigned big-endian byte sequence as an ASN.1 DER INTEGER. The
DER rules require:
  - Tag 0x02
  - Length encoded per X.690 8.1.3
  - Content with no leading zero bytes (canonical form) EXCEPT a single
    leading 0x00 is prepended whenever the high bit of the first content
    byte is set, so the INTEGER is unambiguously non-negative.

Used by the RFC 5915 ECPrivateKey and RFC 8017 RSAPrivateKey encoders.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Find the first non-zero byte in src[0..src_len-1] to strip leading
     zeros from the magnitude.
  2. Decide whether a 0x00 prefix is needed (high bit of the first
     non-zero byte is set, OR the magnitude is zero).
  3. Write tag 0x02, the DER length, the optional prefix byte, then the
     stripped content bytes.
  4. Return total bytes written (tag + length-encoding + content).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(src_len) in the worst case (the leading-zero scan). At RSA-4096 scale
this is at most 512 byte reads per component.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Used on both public and private bigints. For private components the
caller is responsible for secure handling of the output buffer.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_write_der_integer_unsigned" takes out_buffer as Integer, out_offset as Integer, src as Integer, src_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find the index of the first non-zero byte (mag_start). If no
    Note: byte is non-zero, the magnitude is zero.
    Let mag_start be 0
    Let mag_is_zero be 1
    Let scan_index be 0
    While scan_index is less than src_len:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(src, scan_index) is not equal to 0:
            Set mag_start to scan_index
            Set mag_is_zero to 0
            Set scan_index to src_len
        Otherwise:
            Set scan_index to scan_index plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Let content_len be 0
    Let need_zero_prefix be 0
    If mag_is_zero is equal to 1:
        Note: Encode INTEGER 0 as one content byte 0x00.
        Set content_len to 1
        Set need_zero_prefix to 1
    Otherwise:
        Let stripped_len be src_len minus mag_start
        Let first_byte be Memory.memory_get_byte(src, mag_start)
        Let high_bit be first_byte divided by 128
        If high_bit is equal to 1:
            Set need_zero_prefix to 1
            Set content_len to stripped_len plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set content_len to stripped_len
        End If
    End If

    Let header_len be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(content_len)

    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, out_offset, 2)
    Let off be out_offset plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(out_buffer, off, content_len)
    If need_zero_prefix is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, off, 0)
        Set off to off plus 1
    End If
    If mag_is_zero is equal to 0:
        Let copy_len be src_len minus mag_start
        Memory.memory_copy(out_buffer plus off, src plus mag_start, copy_len)
        Set off to off plus copy_len
    End If
    Return header_len plus content_len
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper that returns the number of bytes a DER INTEGER encoding of an
unsigned big-endian magnitude will consume without writing anything.
Used during inside-out size computation of ECPrivateKey / RSAPrivateKey
SEQUENCEs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirrors keypair_write_der_integer_unsigned: strips leading zeros,
decides whether a 0x00 prefix byte is required, sums tag + length
header + content.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(src_len) in the worst case.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_der_integer_unsigned_bytes" takes src as Integer, src_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let mag_start be 0
    Let mag_is_zero be 1
    Let scan_index be 0
    While scan_index is less than src_len:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(src, scan_index) is not equal to 0:
            Set mag_start to scan_index
            Set mag_is_zero to 0
            Set scan_index to src_len
        Otherwise:
            Set scan_index to scan_index plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Let content_len be 0
    If mag_is_zero is equal to 1:
        Set content_len to 1
    Otherwise:
        Let stripped_len be src_len minus mag_start
        Let first_byte be Memory.memory_get_byte(src, mag_start)
        Let high_bit be first_byte divided by 128
        If high_bit is equal to 1:
            Set content_len to stripped_len plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set content_len to stripped_len
        End If
    End If

    Return 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(content_len) plus content_len
