@Implementation
Materializes bn into an arena byte buffer of bigint_byte_length(bn)
bytes, then forwards to keypair_der_integer_unsigned_bytes. For zero
bn, returns the byte count of INTEGER 0 (3: tag + length + zero).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(byte_length).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_der_integer_bigint_bytes" takes arena as Integer, bn as Integer returns Integer:
    Let bn_len be BigInt.bigint_byte_length(bn)
    If bn_len is equal to 0:
        Let zero_buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 1)
        If zero_buf is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zero_buf, 0, 0)
        Return keypair_der_integer_unsigned_bytes(zero_buf, 1)
    End If
    Let mag_buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bn_len)
    If mag_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    BigInt.bigint_to_bytes_be(bn, mag_buf, bn_len)
    Return keypair_der_integer_unsigned_bytes(mag_buf, bn_len)
