@Reasoning
Emit PKCS#8 PrivateKeyInfo for ECDSA private keys per RFC 5208 + RFC 5915.
The privateKey OCTET STRING wraps an ECPrivateKey SEQUENCE:

  ECPrivateKey ::= SEQUENCE {
    version        INTEGER (1),
    privateKey     OCTET STRING,                       -- raw scalar
    parameters [0] EXPLICIT ECParameters OPTIONAL,     -- namedCurve OID
    publicKey  [1] EXPLICIT BIT STRING OPTIONAL        -- uncompressed point
  }

The parameters field is also reflected in the outer AlgorithmIdentifier
parameters (namedCurve OID), so a strict reader sees the curve twice;
this is permitted by both RFC 5208 and RFC 5915 and matches how OpenSSL
emits ECDSA PKCS#8.

The publicKey BIT STRING content is `00 || uncompressed_point` where
the uncompressed_point follows SEC 1: 0x04 || X || Y.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Source the raw scalar (priv_bytes) and the uncompressed public point
     (from the KeyPair's PublicKey side).
  2. Size each ECPrivateKey field inside-out:
     - INTEGER 1               (3 bytes)
     - OCTET STRING scalar     (1 + length-bytes + scalar_len)
     - [0] EXPLICIT namedCurve (2 + curve_oid_len)
     - [1] EXPLICIT BIT STRING (2 + 2 + pub_len) -- inner BIT STRING includes unused-bits prefix
  3. Wrap in an OCTET STRING; wrap that plus version + AlgorithmIdentifier
     in the outer SEQUENCE.
  4. Allocate and emit.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(scalar_len + pub_len). One pass.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The DER blob holds the private scalar; caller is responsible for secure
storage and wipe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_serialize_pkcs8_ecdsa" takes arena as Integer, algorithm as Integer, kp as Integer, priv_bytes as Integer, priv_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let pk be KP.keypair_public(kp)
    If pk is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pub_bytes be PK.public_key_bytes(pk)
    Let pub_len be PK.public_key_byte_length(pk)
    If pub_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let curve_oid_total be keypair_named_curve_oid_bytes(algorithm)
    If curve_oid_total is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ECPrivateKey SEQUENCE sizing (inside-out).
    Let version_total be 3
    Let scalar_octet_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(priv_len) plus priv_len
    Let curve_explicit_content_len be curve_oid_total
    Let curve_explicit_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(curve_explicit_content_len) plus curve_explicit_content_len
    Let bitstring_content_len be 1 plus pub_len
    Let bitstring_inner_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(bitstring_content_len) plus bitstring_content_len
    Let pub_explicit_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(bitstring_inner_total) plus bitstring_inner_total

    Let ec_seq_content_len be version_total plus scalar_octet_total plus curve_explicit_total plus pub_explicit_total
    Let ec_seq_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(ec_seq_content_len) plus ec_seq_content_len

    Note: AlgorithmIdentifier SEQUENCE: id-ecPublicKey OID (9 bytes) + namedCurve OID.
    Let alg_oid_total be 9
    Let alg_extra be curve_oid_total
    Let alg_seq_content_len be alg_oid_total plus alg_extra
    Let alg_seq_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(alg_seq_content_len) plus alg_seq_content_len

    Note: Outer privateKey OCTET STRING wraps the ECPrivateKey SEQUENCE.
    Let priv_octet_content_len be ec_seq_total
    Let priv_octet_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(priv_octet_content_len) plus priv_octet_content_len

    Let pkcs8_version_total be 3
    Let outer_content_len be pkcs8_version_total plus alg_seq_total plus priv_octet_total
    Let outer_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(outer_content_len) plus outer_content_len

    Let buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 4 plus outer_total)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int32(buf, 0, outer_total)
    Let off be 4

    Note: Outer SEQUENCE.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, outer_content_len)

    Note: version INTEGER 0.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 1, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 2, 0)
    Set off to off plus 3

    Note: AlgorithmIdentifier SEQUENCE.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, alg_seq_content_len)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_oid(algorithm, buf, off)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_named_curve_oid(algorithm, buf, off)

    Note: privateKey OCTET STRING.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 4)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, priv_octet_content_len)

    Note: ECPrivateKey SEQUENCE.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, ec_seq_content_len)

    Note:   version INTEGER 1.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 1, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 2, 1)
    Set off to off plus 3

    Note:   privateKey OCTET STRING - raw scalar.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 4)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, priv_len)
    Memory.memory_copy(buf plus off, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    Set off to off plus priv_len

    Note:   [0] EXPLICIT namedCurve OID.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 160)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, curve_explicit_content_len)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_named_curve_oid(algorithm, buf, off)

    Note:   [1] EXPLICIT BIT STRING publicKey.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 161)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, bitstring_inner_total)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 3)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, bitstring_content_len)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 0)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Memory.memory_copy(buf plus off, pub_bytes, pub_len)
    Set off to off plus pub_len

    Return buf
End Process

@Reasoning
Emit PKCS#8 PrivateKeyInfo for RSA private keys per RFC 5208 + RFC 8017.
The privateKey OCTET STRING wraps a PKCS#1 RSAPrivateKey SEQUENCE:

  RSAPrivateKey ::= SEQUENCE {
    version           INTEGER (0),
    modulus           INTEGER (n),
    publicExponent    INTEGER (e),
    privateExponent   INTEGER (d),
    prime1            INTEGER (p),
    prime2            INTEGER (q),
    exponent1         INTEGER (dp = d mod (p - 1)),
    exponent2         INTEGER (dq = d mod (q - 1)),
    coefficient       INTEGER (qinv = q^(-1) mod p)
    -- otherPrimeInfos OPTIONAL, omitted for two-prime RSA
  }

The bignums are extracted from the rsa_private_key holder via the
rsa_private_get_* accessors and materialized as canonical big-endian
INTEGERs (no leading zeros, with a 0x00 prefix when the high bit is
set to preserve non-negative semantics).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Read the rsa_private_key holder pointer from the carried private
     bytes (the in-tree pack layout stores it at offset 28).
  2. Size each INTEGER inside-out via keypair_der_integer_bigint_bytes.
  3. Wrap n..qinv into the inner RSAPrivateKey SEQUENCE.
  4. Wrap that SEQUENCE in an OCTET STRING.
  5. Wrap version + AlgorithmIdentifier(rsaEncryption, NULL) + OCTET
     STRING in the outer PKCS#8 SEQUENCE.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(modulus_bytes). Eight bigint materializations + one final copy.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The DER blob carries all CRT secrets; caller is responsible for secure
storage and wipe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_serialize_pkcs8_rsa" takes arena as Integer, algorithm as Integer, sk as Integer returns Integer:
    Let priv_bytes be SK.private_key_secret_bytes_internal(sk)
    If priv_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let priv_holder be Memory.memory_get_int64(priv_bytes, 28)
    If priv_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let bn_n be Rsa.rsa_private_get_n(priv_holder)
