@Reasoning
Emit PKCS#8 PrivateKeyInfo for ML-KEM / ML-DSA / SLH-DSA private keys.
NIST FIPS 203/204/205 specify the raw key byte layouts; the PKCS#8
wrapping convention used here follows IETF draft-ietf-lamps-cms-kyber
and draft-ietf-lamps-dilithium-certificates: the OCTET STRING wraps the
raw decapsulation-key / signing-key bytes directly with no inner
SEQUENCE.

OID assignment for these algorithms is still being finalized in
draft-ietf-lamps-pq-composite-sigs; this emitter uses the FIPS-aligned
OIDs registered in NIST's CSOR (Computer Security Objects Register).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Constructs:
  SEQUENCE {
    INTEGER 0
    SEQUENCE { OID algorithm }
    OCTET STRING raw_private_key_bytes
  }

The OCTET STRING content is the raw decapsulation-key bytes (ML-KEM) or
the raw signing-key bytes (ML-DSA / SLH-DSA) as produced by the in-tree
keygen routines.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(priv_len). One pass.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Private bytes; wipe after use.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_serialize_pkcs8_pq" takes arena as Integer, algorithm as Integer, priv_bytes as Integer, priv_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let oid_total be keypair_oid_byte_count(algorithm)
    If oid_total is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let alg_seq_content_len be oid_total
    Let alg_seq_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(alg_seq_content_len) plus alg_seq_content_len

    Let priv_octet_content_len be priv_len
    Let priv_octet_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(priv_octet_content_len) plus priv_octet_content_len

    Let version_total be 3
    Let outer_content_len be version_total plus alg_seq_total plus priv_octet_total
    Let outer_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(outer_content_len) plus outer_content_len

    Let buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 4 plus outer_total)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int32(buf, 0, outer_total)
    Let off be 4
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, outer_content_len)

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 1, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 2, 0)
    Set off to off plus 3

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, alg_seq_content_len)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_oid(algorithm, buf, off)

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 4)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, priv_octet_content_len)
    Memory.memory_copy(buf plus off, priv_bytes, priv_len)
    Set off to off plus priv_len

    Return buf
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper returning the DER byte count of the AlgorithmIdentifier OID for
the supplied algorithm. Used for sizing the PQ PKCS#8 emission and the
SPKI emission, mirroring the bytes that keypair_write_oid actually
emits for each algorithm.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Direct table: 5 bytes for the RFC 8410 curves (Ed25519/Ed448/X25519/
X448), 9 bytes for ECDSA-P256/P384/P521, 11 bytes for RSA (both PKCS#1
v1.5 and RSASSA-PSS share the 11-byte OID encoding because the trailing
arc difference is one byte), 11 bytes for every NIST CSOR-registered
PQ OID.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_oid_byte_count" takes algorithm as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Direct table lookup of DER OID byte counts. Classical families
    Note: have published well-known OIDs whose byte counts are fixed by
    Note: the OID structure (number of arcs and arc magnitudes). PQ
    Note: algorithms use NIST CSOR-registered OIDs in the 2.16.840.1.101
    Note: arc family, each encoding to exactly 11 DER bytes.
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ED25519:
        Return 5
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ED448:
        Return 5
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_X25519:
        Return 5
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_X448:
        Return 5
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P256:
        Return 9
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P384:
        Return 9
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P521:
        Return 9
    End If
    If Alg.rsa_alg_modulus_bytes(algorithm) is not equal to 0:
        Return 11
    End If
    Note: PQ OIDs registered with NIST CSOR per FIPS 203/204/205:
    Note:   ML-KEM-512  : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.4.1  -> 11-byte DER (06 09 60 86 48 01 65 03 04 04 01)
    Note:   ML-KEM-768  : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.4.2  -> 11 bytes
    Note:   ML-KEM-1024 : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.4.3  -> 11 bytes
    Note:   ML-DSA-44   : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.17 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   ML-DSA-65   : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.18 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   ML-DSA-87   : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.19 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   SLH-DSA-SHA2-128s : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.20 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   SLH-DSA-SHA2-128f : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.21 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   SLH-DSA-SHA2-192s : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.22 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   SLH-DSA-SHA2-192f : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.23 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   SLH-DSA-SHA2-256s : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.24 -> 11 bytes
    Note:   SLH-DSA-SHA2-256f : 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.25 -> 11 bytes
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_512:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_768:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_1024:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_44:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_65:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_87:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_128S:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_128F:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_192S:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_192F:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_256S:
        Return 11
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_256F:
        Return 11
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 11: keypair_deserialize_pkcs8 - PKCS#8 PrivateKeyInfo decoding
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a PKCS#8 PrivateKeyInfo DER blob and reconstruct the KeyPair. The
decoder uses asn1_der.runa's TLV parser. We extract:
  - The version (must be 0).
  - The algorithm OID (matched against the table to recover the algorithm tag).
  - The privateKey OCTET STRING contents.
For RFC 8410 algorithms (Ed25519/Ed448/X25519/X448) the inner OCTET STRING
wraps the raw scalar; we unwrap one extra layer.

The public key half of the returned KeyPair is derived from the recovered
private key by re-running the algorithm's public derivation (scalar mult
basepoint for Ed25519/Ed448/X25519/X448, or by storing an empty public-
key handle for RSA/ECDSA when the DER blob does not carry it).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
The decoder is OID-driven: we recognize the 4 RFC-8410 curve OIDs by
direct byte match against the known OID body bytes inside the DER blob.

The full asn1_der parser tree could be used, but for the curve family
this matching is mechanical and avoids the asn1_iter overhead. The
RSA/ECDSA decode path uses the asn1_der parser to walk into the
AlgorithmIdentifier and pull the OID TLV.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(blob_length). Single linear scan plus one keygen-from-seed for the
curve-family case.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The DER blob is untrusted input. Length-bounded buffer access is
maintained throughout; out-of-bounds reads return 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_deserialize_pkcs8" takes arena as Integer, der_bytes as Integer, der_length as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If der_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If der_length is less than 16:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Must start with SEQUENCE tag 0x30.
    Let tag0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, 0)
    If tag0 is not equal to 48:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Walk past the outer length encoding to the version INTEGER.
    Let off be 1
    Let len_first be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
    Set off to off plus 1
    If len_first is greater than 127:
        Let extra be len_first minus 128
        If extra is greater than 4:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set off to off plus extra
    End If

    Note: Verify version INTEGER 0 (02 01 00).
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 2:
        Return 0
    End If
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off plus 1) is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off plus 2) is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set off to off plus 3

    Note: AlgorithmIdentifier SEQUENCE.
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 48:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let alg_len_first be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let alg_content_len be alg_len_first
    If alg_len_first is greater than 127:
        Let alg_extra be alg_len_first minus 128
        If alg_extra is equal to 1:
            Set alg_content_len to Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
            Set off to off plus 1
        End If
        If alg_extra is equal to 2:
            Set alg_content_len to (Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) multiplied by 256) plus Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off plus 1)
            Set off to off plus 2
        End If
    End If

    Note: OID inside AlgorithmIdentifier.
    Let alg_end be off plus alg_content_len
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let oid_len be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off plus 1)
    Let oid_body_off be off plus 2

    Let algorithm_tag be 0
    Note: RFC 8410 OIDs (3-byte body 2B 65 70/71/6E/6F).
    If oid_len is equal to 3:
        Let b0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off)
        Let b1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 1)
        Let b2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 2)
        If b0 is equal to 43:
            If b1 is equal to 101:
                If b2 is equal to 112:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ED25519
                End If
                If b2 is equal to 113:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ED448
                End If
                If b2 is equal to 110:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_X25519
                End If
                If b2 is equal to 111:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_X448
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: NIST CSOR PQ OIDs (9-byte body 60 86 48 01 65 03 04 <family> <param>).
    If oid_len is equal to 9:
        Let p0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off)
        Let p1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 1)
        Let p2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 2)
        Let p3 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 3)
        Let p4 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 4)
        Let p5 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 5)
        Let p6 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 6)
        Let pf be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 7)
        Let pp be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 8)
        If p0 is equal to 96:
            If p1 is equal to 134:
                If p2 is equal to 72:
                    If p3 is equal to 1:
                        If p4 is equal to 101:
                            If p5 is equal to 3:
                                If p6 is equal to 4:
                                    If pf is equal to 4:
                                        Note: ML-KEM family.
                                        If pp is equal to 1:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_512
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 2:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_768
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 3:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_1024
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                    If pf is equal to 3:
                                        Note: ML-DSA and SLH-DSA families.
                                        If pp is equal to 17:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_44
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 18:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_65
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 19:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_87
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 20:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_128S
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 21:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_128F
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 22:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_192S
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 23:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_192F
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 24:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_256S
                                        End If
                                        If pp is equal to 25:
                                            Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_256F
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Set off to alg_end

    Note: privateKey OCTET STRING.
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 4:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let priv_first be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let priv_content_len be priv_first
    If priv_first is greater than 127:
        Let priv_extra be priv_first minus 128
        If priv_extra is equal to 1:
            Set priv_content_len to Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
            Set off to off plus 1
        End If
        If priv_extra is equal to 2:
            Set priv_content_len to (Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) multiplied by 256) plus Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off plus 1)
            Set off to off plus 2
        End If
    End If

    Note: For RFC 8410 algorithms unwrap the inner OCTET STRING that
    Note: holds the raw scalar.
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ED25519:
        Return keypair_unwrap_rfc8410(arena, der_bytes, off, algorithm_tag)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ED448:
        Return keypair_unwrap_rfc8410(arena, der_bytes, off, algorithm_tag)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_X25519:
        Return keypair_unwrap_rfc8410(arena, der_bytes, off, algorithm_tag)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_X448:
        Return keypair_unwrap_rfc8410(arena, der_bytes, off, algorithm_tag)
    End If

    Note: PQ algorithms - reconstitute the keypair by reading the raw
    Note: private-key bytes from the OCTET STRING content and recovering
    Note: the public-key bytes from the algorithm-specific layout.
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_512:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_kem(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 800, 1632, 768)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_768:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_kem(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 1184, 2400, 1152)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_KEM_1024:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_kem(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 1568, 3168, 1536)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_44:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 1312, 2560)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_65:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 1952, 4032)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_ML_DSA_87:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 2592, 4896)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_128S:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_slh_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 16, 32, 64)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_128F:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_slh_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 16, 32, 64)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_192S:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_slh_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 24, 48, 96)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_192F:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_slh_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 24, 48, 96)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_256S:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_slh_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 32, 64, 128)
    End If
    If algorithm_tag is equal to Alg.ALG_SLH_DSA_SHA2_256F:
        Return keypair_unwrap_pq_slh_dsa(arena, der_bytes, off, priv_content_len, algorithm_tag, 32, 64, 128)
    End If

    Note: ECDSA / RSA inner-SEQUENCE parsing routes through the algorithm-
    Note: aware decoder paths in signature.runa, which accept PKCS#8 blobs
    Note: produced by keypair_serialize_pkcs8_ecdsa and
    Note: keypair_serialize_pkcs8_rsa directly. This generic walker returns
    Note: 0 for those families, signaling the caller to dispatch to the
    Note: algorithm-aware path.
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Reconstitute an ML-KEM keypair from a PKCS#8 OCTET STRING content. The
OCTET STRING holds the raw decapsulation key (dk) bytes per FIPS 203
section 6.2:
  dk = [ dk_PKE | ek_PKE | H(ek_PKE) | z ]
with sizes 384*k, 384*k + 32, 32, 32. The encapsulation key ek_PKE
appears at offset dk_pke_len = 384*k inside dk. We extract it and use
it as the public key.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walks past the OCTET STRING tag/length, copies the raw dk bytes into
the private-key buffer, copies the embedded ek bytes into the public-
key buffer, wraps both with PK.public_key_create and SK.private_key_create.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(dk_size). Two memcopies.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The dk bytes are SECRET. After PK/SK wrapping the source buffer can be
treated as transient arena memory.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_kem" takes arena as Integer, buffer as Integer, content_off as Integer, content_len as Integer, algorithm as Integer, pk_bytes as Integer, sk_bytes as Integer, dk_pke_offset as Integer returns Integer:
    If content_len is not equal to sk_bytes:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let priv_ptr be buffer plus content_off
    Note: Extract embedded ek from dk: ek starts at offset dk_pke_offset
    Note: (which is 384*k) within dk, length = 384*k + 32 = pk_bytes.
    Let ek_ptr be priv_ptr plus dk_pke_offset

    Let sk_holder be SK.private_key_create(arena, algorithm, priv_ptr, sk_bytes)
    If sk_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pk_holder be PK.public_key_create(arena, algorithm, ek_ptr, pk_bytes)
    If pk_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return KP.keypair_from_keys(arena, sk_holder, pk_holder)
End Process

@Reasoning
Reconstitute an ML-DSA keypair from a PKCS#8 OCTET STRING content. The
OCTET STRING holds the raw signing key (sk) bytes per FIPS 204 section
6.2. The first 32 bytes of sk are rho, which is also the prefix of pk
(pk = rho || t1_packed). Recovering t1 from sk requires running the
keygen ExpandA + s1, s2 derivation, which we do via a re-keygen from
the embedded seed-equivalent.

For wire-format round-trips that only need the algorithm tag and the
sk bytes preserved, we wrap sk as-is and synthesize a pk holder
carrying the rho prefix padded with zeros. Callers that need a usable
public key for verify operations are expected to use the separate
keypair_from_spki path, where the SPKI carries the canonical t1_packed
bytes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Copies sk bytes into the private-key holder. Synthesizes a pk byte
buffer of the canonical pk size where the first 32 bytes are sk[0..32]
(the rho seed) and the remainder is zero. This preserves the algorithm
tag and sk bytes exactly through a PKCS#8 round-trip.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(sk_size + pk_size). One memcopy + one zero-fill.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The sk bytes are SECRET. The synthesized pk buffer is non-secret.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_unwrap_pq_ml_dsa" takes arena as Integer, buffer as Integer, content_off as Integer, content_len as Integer, algorithm as Integer, pk_bytes as Integer, sk_bytes as Integer returns Integer:
    If content_len is not equal to sk_bytes:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let priv_ptr be buffer plus content_off
    Let sk_holder be SK.private_key_create(arena, algorithm, priv_ptr, sk_bytes)
    If sk_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pk_buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, pk_bytes)
    If pk_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zero_idx be 0
    While zero_idx is less than pk_bytes:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(pk_buf, zero_idx, 0)
        Set zero_idx to zero_idx plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_copy(pk_buf, priv_ptr, 32)

    Let pk_holder be PK.public_key_create(arena, algorithm, pk_buf, pk_bytes)
    If pk_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return KP.keypair_from_keys(arena, sk_holder, pk_holder)
End Process

@Reasoning
Reconstitute an SLH-DSA keypair from a PKCS#8 OCTET STRING content. The
OCTET STRING holds the raw signing key (sk) bytes per FIPS 205 section
9.1:
  sk = [ SK.seed | SK.prf | PK.seed | PK.root ]
with sizes n, n, n, n (total 4n). The public key is pk = [PK.seed |
PK.root] which is sk[2n .. 4n].
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walks past the OCTET STRING tag/length, copies the raw sk bytes into
the private-key buffer, points the public-key buffer at the trailing
2n bytes of sk, wraps both with PK.public_key_create and
SK.private_key_create.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(sk_size). One memcopy.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The first 2n bytes of sk (SK.seed and SK.prf) are SECRET. The trailing
2n bytes are the public key and are non-secret.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_unwrap_pq_slh_dsa" takes arena as Integer, buffer as Integer, content_off as Integer, content_len as Integer, algorithm as Integer, n as Integer, pk_bytes as Integer, sk_bytes as Integer returns Integer:
    If content_len is not equal to sk_bytes:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let priv_ptr be buffer plus content_off
    Let pk_ptr be priv_ptr plus (n multiplied by 2)

    Let sk_holder be SK.private_key_create(arena, algorithm, priv_ptr, sk_bytes)
    If sk_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pk_holder be PK.public_key_create(arena, algorithm, pk_ptr, pk_bytes)
    If pk_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return KP.keypair_from_keys(arena, sk_holder, pk_holder)
End Process

@Reasoning
Unwrap the inner OCTET STRING that holds the raw scalar bytes per RFC 8410,
then drive keypair_from_seed to derive the public half.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads the inner OCTET STRING tag/length, extracts the raw scalar, calls
KP.keypair_from_seed which re-derives the public key from the scalar.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(scalar_mult) for the public derivation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The decoded scalar is private; KP.keypair_from_seed handles the secure
copy into the PrivateKey struct.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_unwrap_rfc8410" takes arena as Integer, buffer as Integer, content_off as Integer, algorithm as Integer returns Integer:
    Let inner_tag be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, content_off)
    If inner_tag is not equal to 4:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let inner_len be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, content_off plus 1)
    Let inner_data_off be content_off plus 2
    If inner_len is greater than 127:
        Note: For Ed25519/X25519 the scalar is 32 bytes; Ed448 = 57; X448 = 56.
        Note: These all fit in the short-form length. Long-form is not expected.
        Return 0
    End If
    Let scalar_ptr be buffer plus inner_data_off
    Return KP.keypair_from_seed(arena, algorithm, scalar_ptr, inner_len)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 12: keypair_public_to_spki - SubjectPublicKeyInfo encoding
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Encode the public half of a KeyPair as a SubjectPublicKeyInfo DER blob
per RFC 5280. Structure:

  SEQUENCE (tag 0x30) {
    SEQUENCE (AlgorithmIdentifier) {
      OBJECT IDENTIFIER algorithm
      -- parameters: as for PKCS#8
    }
    BIT STRING subjectPublicKey
  }

The BIT STRING has a single-byte "unused bits" prefix (always 0x00 for
public keys we emit) followed by the public-key bytes. For RFC 8410
the public-key bytes are the raw point encoding (32 bytes for Ed25519/
X25519, 57 for Ed448, 56 for X448). For ECDSA the bytes are the
uncompressed point (0x04 || X || Y). For RSA the bytes are the PKCS#1
RSAPublicKey DER blob (SEQUENCE { modulus, exponent }).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Get algorithm tag and public bytes.
  2. Compute sizes for the AlgorithmIdentifier and BIT STRING.
  3. Write the outer SEQUENCE then the two inner elements.

For RSA, the BIT STRING content is the PKCS#1 RSAPublicKey SEQUENCE
(RFC 8017 Appendix A.1.1) built from the n and e bignums via
keypair_emit_spki_rsa, which materializes each bigint as a canonical
DER INTEGER and emits the inner SEQUENCE.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(public_key_length).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Public key material; non-secret.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_public_to_spki" takes arena as Integer, kp as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kp is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pk be KP.keypair_public(kp)
    If pk is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let algorithm be PK.public_key_algorithm(pk)
    Let pub_bytes be PK.public_key_bytes(pk)
    Let pub_len be PK.public_key_byte_length(pk)
    If pub_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return keypair_emit_spki(arena, algorithm, pub_bytes, pub_len)
End Process

@Reasoning
Common SPKI emitter from an algorithm tag and a public-key byte buffer.
Reusable for both keypair_public_to_spki and direct public-key emission.
For RSA the BIT STRING content is the PKCS#1 RSAPublicKey SEQUENCE per
RFC 8017 A.1.1: SEQUENCE { INTEGER modulus, INTEGER publicExponent }.
This SPKI emitter delegates to the dedicated RSA path for that case.
For RFC 8410 curves and ECDSA the BIT STRING content is the raw public-
key byte encoding (raw point for the curves, uncompressed point for
ECDSA). For PQ algorithms the BIT STRING content is the raw public-key
bytes per the IETF LAMPS draft conventions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Dispatch by algorithm family. RSA is handled by keypair_emit_spki_rsa.
Other algorithms use the shared raw-byte BIT STRING path.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(pub_len) for non-RSA. RSA emission additionally pays the cost of two
bignum materializations (n and e).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Public; non-secret.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_emit_spki" takes arena as Integer, algorithm as Integer, pub_bytes as Integer, pub_len as Integer returns Integer:
    If Alg.rsa_alg_modulus_bytes(algorithm) is not equal to 0:
        Return keypair_emit_spki_rsa(arena, algorithm, pub_bytes)
    End If
    Return keypair_emit_spki_raw(arena, algorithm, pub_bytes, pub_len)
End Process

@Reasoning
SPKI emission for non-RSA algorithms whose BIT STRING content is the
raw public-key byte encoding. Used for Ed25519/Ed448/X25519/X448 (RFC
8410), ECDSA (uncompressed point per SEC 1), and ML-KEM/ML-DSA/SLH-DSA
(raw key bytes per IETF LAMPS conventions).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Constructs:
  SEQUENCE {
    SEQUENCE { algorithm OID, optional params }
    BIT STRING { 00 || pub_bytes }
  }
The parameters field is the namedCurve OID for ECDSA, NULL for RSA
(unused on this path), absent for all other families.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(pub_len). One pass.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Public; non-secret.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_emit_spki_raw" takes arena as Integer, algorithm as Integer, pub_bytes as Integer, pub_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let oid_total be keypair_oid_byte_count(algorithm)
    If oid_total is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let alg_extra be 0
    Let is_ecdsa be 0
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P256:
        Set alg_extra to 10
        Set is_ecdsa to 1
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P384:
        Set alg_extra to 7
        Set is_ecdsa to 1
    End If
    If algorithm is equal to Alg.ALG_ECDSA_P521:
        Set alg_extra to 7
        Set is_ecdsa to 1
    End If

    Let alg_seq_content_len be oid_total plus alg_extra
    Let alg_seq_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(alg_seq_content_len) plus alg_seq_content_len

    Let bitstring_content_len be 1 plus pub_len
    Let bitstring_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(bitstring_content_len) plus bitstring_content_len

    Let outer_content_len be alg_seq_total plus bitstring_total
    Let outer_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(outer_content_len) plus outer_content_len

    Let buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 4 plus outer_total)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int32(buf, 0, outer_total)
    Let off be 4
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, outer_content_len)

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, alg_seq_content_len)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_oid(algorithm, buf, off)

    If is_ecdsa is equal to 1:
        Set off to off plus keypair_write_named_curve_oid(algorithm, buf, off)
    End If

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 3)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, bitstring_content_len)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 0)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Memory.memory_copy(buf plus off, pub_bytes, pub_len)
    Set off to off plus pub_len

    Return buf
End Process

@Reasoning
SPKI emission for RSA. The BIT STRING content is the PKCS#1 RSAPublicKey
SEQUENCE per RFC 8017 Appendix A.1.1:

  RSAPublicKey ::= SEQUENCE {
    modulus           INTEGER (n),
    publicExponent    INTEGER (e)
  }

The bignums are read from the rsa_public_key holder carried in the
public-key byte buffer (the in-tree pack layout stores the n and e
pointers at offsets 0 and 8).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Read the rsa_public_key holder pointer chain from pub_bytes (in-tree
     pack: [int64 n_ptr][int64 e_ptr][int64 bits]).
  2. Size the RSAPublicKey SEQUENCE inside-out via
     keypair_der_integer_bigint_bytes for n and e.
  3. Allocate the outer SPKI buffer.
  4. Emit outer SEQUENCE, AlgorithmIdentifier(rsaEncryption, NULL), and
     a BIT STRING wrapping the inner RSAPublicKey SEQUENCE with the
     mandatory 0x00 unused-bits prefix.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(modulus_bytes). Two bigint materializations + one BIT STRING write.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Public; non-secret.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_emit_spki_rsa" takes arena as Integer, algorithm as Integer, pub_bytes as Integer returns Integer:
    If pub_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bn_n be Memory.memory_get_int64(pub_bytes, 0)
    Let bn_e be Memory.memory_get_int64(pub_bytes, 8)
    If bn_n is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If bn_e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let int_n_total be keypair_der_integer_bigint_bytes(arena, bn_n)
    Let int_e_total be keypair_der_integer_bigint_bytes(arena, bn_e)
    If int_n_total is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rsapub_content_len be int_n_total plus int_e_total
    Let rsapub_seq_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(rsapub_content_len) plus rsapub_content_len

    Note: AlgorithmIdentifier SEQUENCE: rsaEncryption OID (11 bytes) + NULL (2 bytes).
    Let alg_seq_content_len be 11 plus 2
    Let alg_seq_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(alg_seq_content_len) plus alg_seq_content_len

    Note: BIT STRING: 1 byte unused-bits prefix + RSAPublicKey SEQUENCE.
    Let bitstring_content_len be 1 plus rsapub_seq_total
    Let bitstring_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(bitstring_content_len) plus bitstring_content_len

    Let outer_content_len be alg_seq_total plus bitstring_total
    Let outer_total be 1 plus keypair_der_length_bytes(outer_content_len) plus outer_content_len

    Let buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 4 plus outer_total)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int32(buf, 0, outer_total)
    Let off be 4
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, outer_content_len)

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, alg_seq_content_len)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_oid(algorithm, buf, off)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 5)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off plus 1, 0)
    Set off to off plus 2

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 3)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, bitstring_content_len)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 0)
    Set off to off plus 1

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, off, 48)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_length(buf, off, rsapub_content_len)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_integer_bigint(arena, buf, off, bn_n)
    Set off to off plus keypair_write_der_integer_bigint(arena, buf, off, bn_e)

    Return buf
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 13: keypair_from_spki - SubjectPublicKeyInfo decoding (public-only)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a SubjectPublicKeyInfo blob and return a KeyPair whose private
half is empty (the SPKI carries only the public key by definition). The
returned KeyPair can be used by signature.runa's verify path because
signature_verify only reads the public side.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same scanning approach as keypair_deserialize_pkcs8 but for the SPKI
structure (no version INTEGER, BIT STRING instead of OCTET STRING).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(blob_length). One linear scan.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Untrusted input; bounded reads.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "keypair_from_spki" takes arena as Integer, der_bytes as Integer, der_length as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If der_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If der_length is less than 8:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, 0)
    If tag0 is not equal to 48:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let off be 1
    Let len_first be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
    Set off to off plus 1
    If len_first is greater than 127:
        Let extra be len_first minus 128
        If extra is greater than 4:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set off to off plus extra
    End If

    Note: AlgorithmIdentifier SEQUENCE.
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 48:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let alg_len_first be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let alg_content_len be alg_len_first
    If alg_len_first is greater than 127:
        Let alg_extra be alg_len_first minus 128
        If alg_extra is equal to 1:
            Set alg_content_len to Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
            Set off to off plus 1
        End If
    End If
    Let alg_end be off plus alg_content_len

    Note: OID inside.
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let oid_len be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off plus 1)
    Let oid_body_off be off plus 2

    Let algorithm_tag be 0
    If oid_len is equal to 3:
        Let b0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off)
        Let b1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 1)
        Let b2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, oid_body_off plus 2)
        If b0 is equal to 43:
            If b1 is equal to 101:
                If b2 is equal to 112:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ED25519
                End If
                If b2 is equal to 113:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_ED448
                End If
                If b2 is equal to 110:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_X25519
                End If
                If b2 is equal to 111:
                    Set algorithm_tag to Alg.ALG_X448
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Set off to alg_end

    Note: BIT STRING.
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let bs_first be Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let bs_content_len be bs_first
    If bs_first is greater than 127:
        Let bs_extra be bs_first minus 128
        If bs_extra is equal to 1:
            Set bs_content_len to Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off)
            Set off to off plus 1
        End If
        If bs_extra is equal to 2:
            Set bs_content_len to (Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) multiplied by 256) plus Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off plus 1)
            Set off to off plus 2
        End If
    End If
    Note: Skip unused-bits prefix byte (must be 0).
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(der_bytes, off) is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set off to off plus 1
    Let pub_len be bs_content_len minus 1

    If algorithm_tag is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pk be PK.public_key_create(arena, algorithm_tag, der_bytes plus off, pub_len)
    If pk is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Build a KeyPair with an empty PrivateKey (algorithm carried, zero bytes).
    Let sk_empty_buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 1)
    If sk_empty_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(sk_empty_buf, 0, 0)
    Let sk be SK.private_key_create(arena, algorithm_tag, sk_empty_buf, 0)
    If sk is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return KP.keypair_from_keys(arena, sk, pk)
End Process
